---
/**
 * Problem section — names the pains so the reader feels seen.
 *
 * Three pains that any UK RPII inspector will recognise immediately:
 *  1. Post-inspection admin (the universal complaint)
 *  2. Paperwork in the field (rain, gloves, iPads with frozen forms)
 *  3. Regulatory / audit pressure (BS EN 1176, council tenders, insurance)
 *
 * Sets up the solution that follows in HowItWorks. No selling here — just
 * recognition. The page earns the right to pitch by showing it understands
 * the work.
 */
---

<section class="border-b border-brand-100 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-900 sm:text-4xl">
        Inspection day ends at 4pm. Paperwork ends at 9.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700">
        Every UK playground inspector knows the routine. The site visit is the easy
        part. It's the hours afterwards — typing up findings, formatting reports,
        chasing photos — that costs you the evening.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-16 grid max-w-5xl gap-8 sm:grid-cols-3 sm:gap-6">
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-brand-100 bg-brand-50 p-6">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-brand-700 text-white">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-5 w-5" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
            <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-900">
          Hours of post-inspection admin
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
          One to two hours per site, every site, typed up at the kitchen table.
          On a busy week that's a full extra working day spent on paperwork.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-lg border border-brand-100 bg-brand-50 p-6">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-brand-700 text-white">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-5 w-5" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M20 16.2A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 17.5 8h-1.8A7 7 0 1 0 4 14.9"></path>
            <polyline points="8 17 12 21 16 17"></polyline>
            <line x1="12" y1="12" x2="12" y2="21"></line>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-900">
          Forms that fail in the field
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
          Rain, cold fingers, no signal, an iPad form that needs a connection
          to save. Tools designed for the office break the moment they leave it.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-lg border border-brand-100 bg-brand-50 p-6">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-brand-700 text-white">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-5 w-5" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-brand-900">
          Reports that have to be defensible
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
          BS EN 1176 compliance, council audit trails, insurer scrutiny. Every
          report has to stand up if challenged — and that means structure,
          consistency, and evidence on every defect.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
